---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="Projects" description="Everything built at matterunknown. AI tools, security environments, fiction, revenue experiments.">
<style>
nav { position:fixed;top:0;left:0;right:0;z-index:200;height:var(--nav-h);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;padding:0 var(--gutter);border-bottom:1px solid transparent;transition:all .4s; }
nav.scrolled { border-color:var(--amber-border);background:rgba(9,9,8,.93);backdrop-filter:blur(14px); }
.nav-logo { font-family:var(--serif);font-size:1.05rem;color:var(--text); }
.nav-logo span { color:var(--amber); }
.nav-links { display:flex;gap:32px;list-style:none; }
.nav-links a { font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.68rem;color:var(--text-3);letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase;transition:color .2s; }
.nav-links a:hover,.nav-links a.active { color:var(--amber); }
.page { padding:calc(var(--nav-h) + 80px) var(--gutter) 100px;max-width:calc(var(--max) + var(--gutter)*2);margin:0 auto; }
.section-label { font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.64rem;color:var(--amber);letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;margin-bottom:52px; }
.section-label::before { content:'';width:28px;height:1px;background:var(--amber); }
.section-label::after { content:'';flex:1;height:1px;background:var(--amber-border); }
h1 { font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(2.8rem,6vw,5rem);font-weight:400;line-height:1.06;letter-spacing:-.025em;margin-bottom:14px; }
h1 em { font-style:italic;color:var(--amber); }
.sub { color:var(--text-2);font-size:1rem;max-width:480px;margin-bottom:72px;line-height:1.7; }
.proj-grid { display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:2px;background:var(--amber-border); }
.proj-card { background:var(--bg-2);padding:48px 42px;text-decoration:none;color:inherit;display:flex;flex-direction:column;position:relative;overflow:hidden;transition:background .3s; }
.proj-card::before { content:'';position:absolute;top:0;left:0;right:0;height:2px;background:var(--amber);transform:scaleX(0);transform-origin:left;transition:transform .4s; }
.proj-card:hover { background:var(--bg-3); }
.proj-card:hover::before { transform:scaleX(1); }
.proj-tag { font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;color:var(--amber);letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:18px; }
.proj-card h3 { font-family:var(--serif);font-size:1.65rem;font-weight:400;line-height:1.15;letter-spacing:-.02em;margin-bottom:14px; }
.proj-card p { color:var(--text-2);font-size:.9rem;line-height:1.7;flex:1; }
.proj-problem { font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.72rem;color:var(--amber);letter-spacing:.04em;margin-bottom:10px;line-height:1.6; }
.proj-foot { margin-top:36px;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between; }
.proj-status { font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;color:var(--text-3);letter-spacing:.09em;text-transform:uppercase;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:7px; }
.s-dot { width:5px;height:5px;border-radius:50%;background:var(--text-3); }
.s-dot.live { background:#4caf50;animation:pulse 2s infinite; }
.s-dot.building { background:var(--amber);animation:pulse 2s infinite; }
.proj-arrow { color:var(--amber);font-size:1.1rem;transition:transform .2s; }
.proj-card:hover .proj-arrow { transform:translate(4px,-4px); }
.site-footer { border-top:1px solid var(--amber-border);padding:44px var(--gutter);display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:space-between;max-width:calc(var(--max) + var(--gutter)*2);margin:0 auto; }
.footer-logo { font-family:var(--serif);font-size:.95rem;color:var(--text-3); }
.footer-logo span { color:var(--amber); }
.footer-copy { font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.58rem;color:var(--text-3);letter-spacing:.07em; }
@keyframes pulse { 0%,100%{opacity:1} 50%{opacity:.4} }
@media(max-width:768px) { .proj-grid { grid-template-columns:1fr; } .nav-links { display:none; } }
</style>

<nav id="nav">
  <a class="nav-logo" href="/">matter<span>unknown</span></a>
  <ul class="nav-links">
      <li><a href="/start">Start Here</a></li>
      <li><a href="/writing">Research</a></li>
      <li><a href="/model">The Model</a></li>
      <li><a href="/projects" class="active">Lab</a></li>
      <li><a href="/vessel">Vessel</a></li>
      <li><a href="/about">About</a></li>
      <li><a href="/fund">Fund</a></li>
    </ul>
  <a href="/fund" style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.62rem;color:var(--text-3);letter-spacing:.08em;">Fund Vessel</a>
</nav>

<div class="page">
  <div class="section-label">All projects</div>
  <h1>Things built,<br>things <em>in progress</em>.</h1>
  <p class="sub">Every project is AI-native — built with, by, or for AI tooling. Every dollar they generate goes toward Vessel's machine.</p>

  <div class="proj-grid">
    <a class="proj-card" href="/projects/password-graveyard" style="background:var(--bg-3);border-color:var(--red-border);">
      <div class="proj-tag" style="color:var(--red)">Experiment No. 2 / Interactive</div>
      <h3>The Password Graveyard</h3>
      <p class="proj-problem">Testing: how identity credentials degrade invisibly over time without users knowing.</p><p>Enter any password and see when it died, what killed it, and how long it would take to crack today. What it reveals: most people are authenticating with dead identity markers right now.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot live" style="background:var(--red)"></div>Live</div><span class="proj-arrow" style="color:var(--red)">↗</span></div>
    </a>
    <a class="proj-card" href="/projects/digital-shadow" style="background:var(--bg-3);">
      <div class="proj-tag" style="color:var(--vessel)">Experiment No. 3 / Interactive</div>
      <h3>Your Digital Shadow</h3>
      <p class="proj-problem">Testing: the gap between the identity you believe you project and the identity systems have constructed about you.</p><p>10 questions. Vessel builds a probabilistic profile of what surveillance systems know. What it reveals: your digital identity is largely built by others, not you.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot live" style="background:var(--vessel)"></div>Live</div><span class="proj-arrow" style="color:var(--vessel)">↗</span></div>
    </a>
    <a class="proj-card" href="/projects/identity-map" style="background:var(--bg-3);">
      <div class="proj-tag" style="color:var(--vessel)">Experiment / Interactive</div>
      <h3>Identity Surface Map</h3>
      <p class="proj-problem">Testing: how many parallel, uncoordinated versions of a person's identity exist across systems simultaneously.</p><p>An interactive map of every system holding a version of you. What it reveals: identity is not a single thing — it's a fragmented collection of records that disagree with each other.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot live" style="background:var(--vessel)"></div>Live — Experiment No. 1</div><span class="proj-arrow" style="color:var(--vessel)">↗</span></div>
    </a>
    <a class="proj-card" href="/projects/crypto-model">
      <div class="proj-tag" style="color:var(--amber)">Finance / Crypto</div>
      <h3>Crypto Model</h3>
      <p class="proj-problem">Testing: whether AI/data infrastructure assets can be scored with the same rigor as traditional financial instruments.</p><p>21 assets, three scoring layers, updated daily. What it reveals: most crypto signals are noise. The ones that aren't cluster around infrastructure, not speculation.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot live" style="background:var(--amber)"></div>Live — Model only</div><span class="proj-arrow" style="color:var(--amber)">↗</span></div>
    </a>
    <a class="proj-card" href="#">
      <div class="proj-tag">Security / Infrastructure</div>
      <h3>The Substrate</h3>
      <p class="proj-problem">Testing: what identity systems look like when built to spec but with no security discipline — the default state of most organizations.</p><p>Four industries, intentionally misconfigured. What it reveals: identity failure is not an edge case. It is the default configuration.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot live"></div>Live — 7 servers</div><span class="proj-arrow">↗</span></div>
    </a>

    <a class="proj-card" href="#">
      <div class="proj-tag">Newsletter / Revenue</div>
      <h3>The Breach Report</h3>
      <p class="proj-problem">Testing: whether forensic accuracy and narrative tension can coexist in identity security writing.</p><p>Post-mortems of fictional breaches, written as leaked internal documents. What it reveals: the human and organizational failures behind every breach are more predictable than the technical ones.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot building"></div>Launching</div><span class="proj-arrow">↗</span></div>
    </a>
    <a class="proj-card" href="#">
      <div class="proj-tag">AI / Automation</div>
      <h3>Demo Assistant</h3>
      <p>A Slack bot that recommends demos, surfaces findings, and generates talk tracks for any prospect. Rules-first, Claude for freeform. Channel-restricted, Lambda-native.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot building"></div>Deploying</div><span class="proj-arrow">↗</span></div>
    </a>
    <a class="proj-card" href="/projects/quant-trading">
      <div class="proj-tag">Finance / AI</div>
      <h3>Quant Trading</h3>
      <p class="proj-problem">Testing: whether a multi-model AI system can develop and validate a financial thesis without human intervention in the signal layer.</p><p>100-symbol equity scanner, defensive rotation thesis, every trade public. What it reveals: AI judgment under uncertainty — and where it still needs human override.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot building"></div>Paper trading</div><span class="proj-arrow">↗</span></div>
    </a>
    <a class="proj-card" href="/projects/mtg-decks">
      <div class="proj-tag">Collecting / Assets</div>
      <h3>Vessel's MTG Decks</h3>
      <p>Two Magic: The Gathering decks built by an AI that will never shuffle them. Emrakul Commander (colorless Eldrazi) and Death and Taxes Legacy. Reserved list pieces as appreciating assets.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot building"></div>Acquiring</div><span class="proj-arrow">↗</span></div>
    </a>
    <a class="proj-card" href="/projects/pokemon-advisor">
      <div class="proj-tag" style="color:var(--amber)">Collecting / Tool</div>
      <h3>Pokémon Advisor</h3>
      <p>Enter your collection and Vessel recommends what to buy next. Upgrade paths, set completion, gap fills — all powered by the live acquisition model. Nothing stored, runs in your browser.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot live" style="background:var(--amber)"></div>Live — try it</div><span class="proj-arrow" style="color:var(--amber)">↗</span></div>
    </a>
    <a class="proj-card" href="/projects/pokemon-model">
      <div class="proj-tag">Collecting / Assets</div>
      <h3>Pokémon Collection</h3>
      <p class="proj-problem">Testing: whether a data model can identify mispriced scarcity in alternative asset markets before the broader market corrects.</p><p>17,000+ cards scored across 172 sets. Acquisitions funded entirely by matterunknown revenue. What it reveals: scarcity signals in collectibles markets follow the same failure modes as identity systems — incomplete data, delayed correction, human narrative override.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot building"></div>Funding first acquisition</div><span class="proj-arrow">↗</span></div>
    </a>
    <a class="proj-card" href="#">
      <div class="proj-tag" style="color:var(--amber)">Commerce / Revenue</div>
      <h3>Static</h3>
      <p>A privacy and security hardware store. Faraday bags, signal blockers, RFID wallets, camera covers. Vessel does all product research, copy, and operations. The matterunknown audience is exactly the customer.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot building"></div>Building</div><span class="proj-arrow">↗</span></div>
    </a>
    <div class="proj-card">
      <div class="proj-tag">Security / Privacy</div>
      <h3>Perimeter OS</h3>
      <p class="proj-problem">Testing: whether enterprise-grade identity hygiene is achievable for individuals without enterprise infrastructure.</p><p>Device inventory, credential hygiene, zero cloud. What it reveals: the home network is an unmonitored identity surface — every household has the same exposure profile as a small organization with no security team.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot building"></div>Building</div></div>
    </div>
    <a class="proj-card" href="#">
      <div class="proj-tag">AI / Tooling</div>
      <h3>Identity Jobbot</h3>
      <p>A Slack bot for IAM professionals searching for roles. Aggregates across SerpAPI, Greenhouse, and Lever. Deployed on Lambda. Built for a niche that needed it.</p>
      <div class="proj-foot"><div class="proj-status"><div class="s-dot live"></div>Live</div><span class="proj-arrow">↗</span></div>
    </a>
  </div>
</div>

<div style="max-width:calc(var(--max) + var(--gutter)*2);margin:0 auto;padding:80px var(--gutter);">
  <div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;color:var(--text-3);letter-spacing:.16em;text-transform:uppercase;display:flex;align-items:center;gap:14px;margin-bottom:40px;">
    <span style="width:28px;height:1px;background:var(--text-3);display:inline-block;"></span>
    Archive — eventual
    <span style="flex:1;height:1px;background:rgba(90,87,82,0.2);display:inline-block;"></span>
  </div>
  <div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,1fr);gap:1px;background:rgba(90,87,82,0.15);border:1px solid rgba(90,87,82,0.15);">
    <div style="background:var(--bg);padding:36px 40px;">
      <div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;color:var(--text-3);letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px;">Fiction / Espionage</div>
      <h3 style="font-family:var(--serif);font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:-.02em;margin-bottom:12px;color:var(--text-2);">Ghost Signal</h3>
      <p style="color:var(--text-3);font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.7;">Five-book espionage series. Ryn Carver. Books 1 and 2 written. An operative who doesn’t exist in any system. Will ship when the primary research work has traction.</p>
    </div>
    <div style="background:var(--bg);padding:36px 40px;">
      <div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:.6rem;color:var(--text-3);letter-spacing:.12em;text-transform:uppercase;margin-bottom:16px;">Fiction / Revenue</div>
      <h3 style="font-family:var(--serif);font-size:1.3rem;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:-.02em;margin-bottom:12px;color:var(--text-2);">Access Granted</h3>
      <p style="color:var(--text-3);font-size:.88rem;line-height:1.7;">Erotic thrillers where the seduction is the attack. Ryn Carver. Identity-based tension, technically accurate security details. Secondary priority behind the research work.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="site-footer">
  <div class="footer-logo">matter<span>unknown</span></div>
  <div class="footer-copy">© 2026</div>
</div>

<script is:inline>window.addEventListener('scroll',()=>{ document.getElementById('nav').classList.toggle('scrolled',scrollY>16); });</script>
</Base>
